  "id": "",
  "summary": "Heavily obfuscated code across dozens of bundled modules",
  "details": "The package ships a `.ad/` directory containing 40+ JavaScript files (x0.js through xz.js plus from-generator.js, phone-validator.js, sms-providers.js, smtp-health-cache.js, web-command.js) that are heavily obfuscated using hex-identifier minification (`_0x\u003chex\u003e` symbol naming consistent with javascript-obfuscator output). The volume and uniformity of obfuscation across many small modules is unusual for a normal library and reduces auditability. The filename themes (phone-validator, sms-providers, smtp-health-cache, web-command) suggest messaging/SMS/SMTP-adjacent functionality. Without traced behavior of these obfuscated modules — confirming whether they perform legitimate library work, contact attacker-controlled endpoints, scrape credentials, or fetch remote payloads — intent cannot be determined from the obfuscation pattern alone. Routing to human review so a reviewer can de-obfuscate the `.ad/` modules, verify destination endpoints, and confirm whether installer-side data flow exists.",
